<p data-start="51" data-end="141">It's the application you use to work with <strong data-start="93" data-end="117">Microsoft SQL Server</strong>. Think of it like this:</p>
<ul data-start="143" data-end="287">
<li data-start="143" data-end="209">
<p data-start="145" data-end="209"><strong data-start="145" data-end="159">SQL Server</strong> = the database engine (where your data is stored)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="210" data-end="287">
<p data-start="212" data-end="287"><strong data-start="212" data-end="220">SSMS</strong> = the interface (where you write SQL queries and manage databases)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="289" data-end="300">Example</h3>
<p data-start="302" data-end="342">Suppose you have a table called <code data-start="334" data-end="341">Sales</code>.</p>
