</li>
<li data-start="986" data-end="1016">
<p data-start="989" data-end="1016">Import your Excel/CSV data.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1018" data-end="1057">
<p data-start="1021" data-end="1057">Run SQL queries to analyze the data.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1059" data-end="1107">
<p data-start="1062" data-end="1107">Use those results in your Power BI dashboard.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<h3 data-start="1109" data-end="1127">Simple analogy</h3>
<p data-start="1129" data-end="1147">Imagine a library:</p>
<ul data-start="1148" data-end="1305">
<li data-start="1148" data-end="1213">
<p data-start="1150" data-end="1213">📚 <strong data-start="1153" data-end="1167">SQL Server</strong> = the library where all the books are stored.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1214" data-end="1305">
<p data-start="1216" data-end="1305">👩‍💻 <strong data-start="1222" data-end="1230">SSMS</strong> = the librarian's desk where you search for, organize, and retrieve books.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1307" data-end="1381">You don't interact directly with the storage room—you use the desk (SSMS).</p>
