ge+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="93">I know exactly what's happening. This is a <strong data-start="43" data-end="64">very common issue</strong> with the Superstore dataset.</p>
<h3 data-start="95" data-end="105">Error:</h3>
<blockquote data-start="106" data-end="155">
<p data-start="108" data-end="155"><strong data-start="108" data-end="155">Column 'Profit' does not allow DBNull.Value</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="157" data-end="298">This means <strong data-start="168" data-end="208">one or more rows have an empty value</strong> in the <code data-start="216" data-end="224">Profit</code> column, but during import SQL Server is not allowing blank (NULL) values.</p>
<p data-start="300" data-end="399">Even though Excel didn't show blanks, sometimes CSV files contain empty values that aren't obvious.</p>
<h2 data-start="401" data-end="433">Fix 1 (Fastest - Recommended)</h2>
<p data-start="435" data-end="474">Go back to the <strong data-start="450" data-end="468">Modify Columns</strong> page.</p>
<p data-start="476" data-end="492">For the columns:</p>
<ul data-start="493" data-end="542">
<li data-start="493" data-end="503">
<p data-start="495" data-end="503"><code data-start="495" data-end="503">Profit</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="504" data-end="513">
<p data-start="506" data-end="513"><code data-start="506" data-end="513">Sales</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="514" data-end="526">
<p data-start="516" data-end="526"><code data-start="516" data-end="526">Discount</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="527" data-end="542">
<p data-start="529" data-end="542"><code data-start="529" data-end="542">Postal_Code</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="544" data-end="578">✅ <strong data-start="546" data-end="577">Check the "Allow Nulls" box</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="580" data-end="598">Then import again.</p>
<hr data-start="600" data-end="603">
<h2 data-start="605" data-end="625">If it still fails</h2>
<p data-start="627" data-end="689">We'll verify whether there are hidden blank values in the CSV.</p>
<p data-start="691" data-end="700">In Excel:</p>
<ol data-start="702" data-end="818">
<li data-start="702" data-end="734">
<p data-start="705" data-end="734">Select the <strong data-start="716" data-end="726">Profit</strong> column.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="735" data-end="757">
<p data-start="738" data-end="757">Press <strong data-start="744" data-end="756">Ctrl + G</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="758" data-end="779">
<p data-start="761" data-end="779">Click <strong data-start="767" data-end="778">Special</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="780" data-end="801">
<p data-start="783" data-end="801">Select <strong data-start="790" data-end="800">Blanks</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="802" data-end="818">
<p data-start="805" data-end="818">Click <strong data-start="811" data-end="817">OK</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="820" data-end="969">If Excel highlights any cells, those are blank. Enter <code data-start="874" data-end="877">0</code> in the first selected cell and press <strong data-start="915" data-end="931">Ctrl + Enter</strong> to fill all selected blanks with <code data-start="965" data-end="968">0</code>.</p>
<hr data-start="971" data-end="974">
<h3 data-start="976" data-end="1004">First, try the easy fix:</h3>
<p data-start="1006" data-end="1093">✔️ Go back to the import wizard.<br>
✔️ Tick <strong data-start="1047" data-end="1062">Allow Nulls</strong> for <code data-start="1067" data-end="1075">Profit</code>.<br>
✔️ Import again.</p>
<p data-start="1095" data-end="1127"><strong data-start="1095" data-end="1127">Tell me whether it succeeds.</strong></p>
